column5: Welcome Aadil....awesome walleye!  I'm in Dryden, fish mostly William's Bay in the summer (Lac Seul)
Welcome Aadil, some beauty eyes there! we gotta go chase some chrome sometime, its ians bud ron btw!
Great intro, those walleye are monsters! Nice job, can't wait to get out to Quinte myself this winter!  Thanks for the post.
Very nice crop of fish thanks for sharing and welcome to the board.    Art

sweet jayzus those are some nice fish you got there  and welcome !  As well, I now think the bar for introductions has been set to a new high, quite possibly unattainable for mere mortals. I'm sure all new members following you, send their thanks lol

Hi Everyone,  Just joined this great looking board, it was recommended to me by Superdad   My name's Aadil and I live and fish on the Bay of Quinte. I attend Fleming College in Lindsay, Ontario. This past Summer I had the great opportunity to work up in Northwestern Ontario at a great lodge as Customer Service/Fishing Guide, so fishing was AWESOME all summer. Just skimmed through a couple of posts and Ben Beattie is on here!! See ya at the lodge next spring buddy, or if your down my way for ice fishing this winter!! Hope I can learn and contribute my knowledge to the board. Here are some pictures of quinte eyes I've caught in the past 2 years or so from what I have on this computer                     My PB 2 years back through the ice    Aadil
I think this may be the best introduction of all times! Thanks for the fish porn, it's always appreciated!  Where abouts in NW ontario are you working at? (Lac Seul?)  Welcome aboard!!!!
Wow!!! Now THAT'S a way to introduce yourself!  Some monsters there.  Welcome to the board...looking forward to reading more of your reports already!
Welcome!
Welcome and great intro.
Welcome to OFC Aadil Glad to meet you. I hope to get up to Quinte next year.Those are some awesome looking fish.  Paul
Welcome, nice walleyes and I especially love the silver one, a grand intro if i do say
Aadil!!  Welcome and great pics buddy.  Some real Quinte pigs there... LOVE IT!!
Welcome aboard Quinteprince.   Beauty fish there, you've got them dialled in
Some medium sized walleye and a little trout eh. Well, maybe you can pick-up some tips here to help.
Thanks for the warm welcome guys   .. Looking forward to sharing some reports in time to come  manitoubass, yes it is on Lac Seul.  Aadil    p.s. you guys have some cool emicons!
Welcome aboard brother...  How about some Gar-pike on the fly next summer????

Definately Bud, I have many monsters come in my backyard to spawn off our dock and canal that runs in our property ... I've caught some monsters in the Napanee River in the spring also. Just let me know when you want to fish for them in the spring and I can easily set you up. Italo did a show here, and all the spots in his show were within eye sight of our dock.  Aadil
welcome aadil !!! some awesome quinte eyes you got there...!!!
A gentleman indeed (good to see here). Anytime steelhead tickles your fancy let me know Aadil and I should be happy to put you on some water. Cheers Bro.
Welcome. Thanks for sharing those pics. Some very, very nice fish there for sure.
A very warm welcome QP!  I look foward to some of your posts this winter
Welcome Aadil.  Great looking fish there and we'd love to hear (and see) about your North-Western Ontario adventures.
Welcome aboard Aadil!  Looks like you have them BOQ eyes dialed in Thanks for sharing the pics! Leechman
Hello from WNY.......VERY NICE FISH...  when the fish fry....
there's no place like quinte.
Some giants there. Nice fish and welcome.
WOW...NICE FISH. FISHED QUITE A BIT IN QUINTY, NOT SO MUCH ANYMORE...GOT THE SALMON ON THE BRAIN FOR NOW WELCOME ABOARD
wow thanks for sharing, does anyone ever catch small ones there ?
Yes, some of is do. We just don't tell anyone.
